WEBVTT

00:06.173 --> 00:09.176
<i>[pensive instrumental music]</i>

00:09.176 --> 00:16.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:23.065 --> 00:26.110
<i>[woman singing in Norwegian]</i>

00:26.110 --> 00:33.117
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:45.796 --> 00:52.803
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:09.612 --> 01:13.032
<i>[thunder booming]</i>

01:13.032 --> 01:15.993
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

01:15.993 --> 01:17.578
<i>Tumang...</i>

01:17.578 --> 01:18.913
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:18.913 --> 01:21.207
...Earther,

01:21.207 --> 01:24.376
who you <i>pashang</i> think
you is?

01:24.376 --> 01:26.962
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:26.962 --> 01:28.130
[people yelling]

01:28.130 --> 01:29.965
[thunder booming]

01:29.965 --> 01:31.967
[people yelling]

01:31.967 --> 01:33.219
[guns cocking]

01:33.219 --> 01:35.137
[thunder booming]

01:35.137 --> 01:37.139
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:37.139 --> 01:38.474
[man] Hey! Hey!

01:38.474 --> 01:40.559
[Wei] Everybody back up.

01:40.559 --> 01:43.103
Back the fuck up.

01:43.103 --> 01:50.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:51.821 --> 01:53.614
[thunder booming]

01:53.614 --> 01:54.990
[Chiwewe] My God, what...

01:54.990 --> 01:56.826
what did you do?

01:58.077 --> 01:59.954
He fucking killed Coop.

02:01.205 --> 02:02.665
You <i>gonya</i> kill us all?

02:03.749 --> 02:07.378
[thunder booming]

02:09.004 --> 02:11.423
<i>[Naomi] The lightning
is moving in a straight line.</i>

02:11.423 --> 02:14.426
[computer beeping]

02:14.426 --> 02:21.433
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:23.936 --> 02:26.272
Amos, you've got lightning
coming your way.

02:26.272 --> 02:27.356
It's gonna hit the settlement.

02:27.356 --> 02:29.024
Amos, get to cover now.

02:29.024 --> 02:30.609
How do you know where
lightning's gonna strike?

02:30.609 --> 02:33.070
[thunder booming]

02:33.070 --> 02:36.866
[all screaming]

02:36.866 --> 02:38.659
[electricity sparking]

02:38.659 --> 02:41.662
[thunder booming]

02:41.662 --> 02:44.206
[people shouting]

02:47.793 --> 02:49.295
<i>[Holden] Amos.
[Naomi] Amos!</i>

02:49.295 --> 02:51.213
I'm here.

02:51.213 --> 02:52.756
What the hell was that?

02:52.756 --> 02:54.133
We're not exactly sure.

02:54.133 --> 02:55.509
Miller turned something on.

02:55.509 --> 02:56.635
<i>[Amos] That sounds bad.</i>

02:56.635 --> 02:57.636
Is everyone okay?

02:57.636 --> 02:59.054
<i>[Amos] More or less.</i>

02:59.054 --> 03:01.807
Power's out
all over the place here.

03:01.807 --> 03:04.268
The RCE stuff's
coming back on.

03:04.268 --> 03:06.437
The Belters
got the worst of it.

03:06.437 --> 03:08.772
<i>[Alex] Sounds like
we all dodged a bullet.</i>

03:08.772 --> 03:11.275
Well, most of us did.

03:11.275 --> 03:13.569
Murphy shot one of the Belters.

03:13.569 --> 03:14.945
What?

03:14.945 --> 03:16.947
- Why?
<i>[Amos] I don't know.</i>

03:16.947 --> 03:19.491
I didn't see how it started,
only the end of it.

03:19.491 --> 03:21.952
The Belter wasn't armed,
but it was three to one.

03:21.952 --> 03:23.454
God damn it.

03:23.454 --> 03:25.289
Murphy shot an unarmed man
in cold blood

03:25.289 --> 03:26.874
and no one did anything?

03:26.874 --> 03:30.002
The lightning blew
this place up right after.

03:30.002 --> 03:32.963
First things last, I guess.

03:32.963 --> 03:35.341
I don't think it's a good idea
to leave here now.

03:35.341 --> 03:37.509
<i>[Holden] Amos, keep a lid
on the situation.</i>

03:37.509 --> 03:39.136
Okay, you want me
to shoot Morty?

03:39.136 --> 03:40.721
No, I don't want anyone
to shoot anyone.

03:40.721 --> 03:42.389
Just do what you can.

03:43.891 --> 03:46.518
<i>[Naomi] The settlers
will need help with repairs.</i>

03:46.518 --> 03:48.646
Amos, I'm gonna grab
whatever spare power modules

03:48.646 --> 03:50.314
we've got on the <i>Roci</i>
and join you there.

03:50.314 --> 03:52.024
[device beeps]

03:52.024 --> 03:53.651
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:53.651 --> 03:55.027
What do you want us to do?

03:55.027 --> 03:58.822
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:58.822 --> 04:00.240
[people yelling]

04:00.240 --> 04:01.742
[man] I'll be right back!

04:02.451 --> 04:04.078
Secure our modules.

04:04.078 --> 04:07.039
No one lifts a finger
to help them.

04:07.039 --> 04:14.046
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:17.758 --> 04:20.302
[device beeps]

04:20.302 --> 04:23.514
[indistinct radio chatter]

04:23.514 --> 04:25.307
Miller told me I was
connecting a circuit.

04:25.307 --> 04:27.434
He didn't say
a goddamn thing about this.

04:27.434 --> 04:29.269
[sighs]

04:29.269 --> 04:31.355
You, uh, want a minute
alone with him?

04:31.355 --> 04:32.982
I mean,
maybe he can explain...

04:32.982 --> 04:34.900
If Miller knew
or cared about us,

04:34.900 --> 04:36.485
he would have warned me
about the settlement.

04:37.778 --> 04:40.114
I'm not sure
I can trust him anymore.

04:40.114 --> 04:42.366
I think
we're on our own.

04:42.366 --> 04:44.410
Fan-fucking-tastic.

04:44.410 --> 04:46.578
Naomi, we need to see
if we can figure out

04:46.578 --> 04:48.330
how to turn off
what I just turned on.

04:49.081 --> 04:50.791
The swarm was bad enough.

04:50.791 --> 04:53.210
This feels a whole
shitload worse.

04:53.210 --> 04:54.920
<i>It has to be the priority.</i>

04:54.920 --> 04:56.338
All right, keep me in the loop.

04:56.338 --> 04:57.172
<i>[Holden] Will do.
Stay safe.</i>

04:57.172 --> 04:58.340
You too.

04:59.425 --> 05:00.467
[sighs]

05:01.552 --> 05:04.680
[breathing heavily]

05:04.680 --> 05:05.681
[groans softly]

05:05.681 --> 05:08.475
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:08.475 --> 05:11.228
- [device clicks]
- [groans]

05:11.228 --> 05:12.646
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:12.646 --> 05:15.024
[device beeping]

05:15.024 --> 05:21.989
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:22.781 --> 05:24.408
[device beeps]

05:24.408 --> 05:31.373
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:31.373 --> 05:33.125
[indistinct chatter]

05:33.125 --> 05:35.127
[man] She go after you.

05:35.127 --> 05:37.129
[man] Earther murderers.

05:37.129 --> 05:40.132
[indistinct chatter]

05:52.019 --> 05:53.187
<i>[Fayez] The lightning's
continuing out</i>

05:53.187 --> 05:54.313
<i>across the ocean.</i>

05:54.313 --> 05:57.983
One strike every 3.71 seconds,

05:57.983 --> 06:00.319
<i>exactly 3.22 kilometers apart.</i>

06:00.319 --> 06:02.654
It's too consistent
to be a natural phenomenon.

06:02.654 --> 06:04.448
<i>Something has
to be creating it.</i>

06:04.448 --> 06:05.824
<i>And get this.</i>

06:05.824 --> 06:07.284
Each strike is a superposition

06:07.284 --> 06:08.952
of 13 separate discharges.

06:08.952 --> 06:11.121
It has to be one
for each moon, right?

06:11.121 --> 06:13.499
Not that I have any idea
what the hell that means.

06:13.499 --> 06:16.210
Elvi, what's wrong?

06:16.210 --> 06:18.253
Chief Murtry.

06:19.588 --> 06:21.632
He shot one of the Belters.

06:21.632 --> 06:27.137
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:27.137 --> 06:28.555
[computer beeps]

06:28.555 --> 06:30.808
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:30.808 --> 06:31.850
My God.

06:31.850 --> 06:33.018
<i>Why?</i>

06:33.018 --> 06:35.104
I don't know.

06:35.104 --> 06:36.939
I think he thought the man

06:36.939 --> 06:39.483
may have had something to do
with the crash.

06:39.483 --> 06:41.527
So he just killed him?

06:41.527 --> 06:42.986
<i>Just like that?</i>

06:42.986 --> 06:44.613
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:44.613 --> 06:46.240
<i>Maybe you should
come back up here.</i>

06:46.240 --> 06:48.200
One of the light shuttles
will be coming down

06:48.200 --> 06:49.785
<i>on a supply run soon.</i>

06:49.785 --> 06:51.662
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:51.662 --> 06:54.164
No.
No.

06:54.164 --> 06:55.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:55.666 --> 06:57.835
We came a long way.

06:57.835 --> 07:00.170
I stayed down here
for a reason.

07:00.170 --> 07:03.882
<i>Can you tell me,
where did the lightning start?</i>

07:03.882 --> 07:05.968
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:05.968 --> 07:09.012
The sensors
first picked it up...

07:09.012 --> 07:10.139
<i>here.</i>

07:10.139 --> 07:11.306
[computer beeps]

07:11.306 --> 07:16.812
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:16.812 --> 07:19.231
Mr. Holden, it's Dr. Okoye.

07:19.231 --> 07:20.899
I'm a little busy right now,
Doctor.

07:20.899 --> 07:22.484
<i>[Elvi]
The lightning phenomenon</i>

07:22.484 --> 07:24.403
<i>seems to have started
at the ruins.</i>

07:24.403 --> 07:26.196
<i>[Holden] I'm aware.</i>
- We need to go there now.

07:26.196 --> 07:27.364
<i>[Holden] I'm already there.</i>

07:27.364 --> 07:28.991
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:28.991 --> 07:31.076
How...how did you get there
so quickly?

07:31.076 --> 07:32.911
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:32.911 --> 07:36.373
Uh, 'cause we're celebrities?

07:36.373 --> 07:37.916
I'll...I'll see you there.

07:37.916 --> 07:40.252
Uh, no, Doctor,
it's really not necessary.

07:40.252 --> 07:43.130
<i>[Elvi] I'm coming.
I'll be there soon.</i>

07:43.130 --> 07:48.343
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:48.343 --> 07:51.346
[engines whirring]

07:56.852 --> 07:59.396
<i>[Gao] Secretary Avasarala
is part of the old guard,</i>

07:59.396 --> 08:02.191
and we can't afford to let this
be an old guard moment.

08:02.191 --> 08:05.152
<i>These worlds are a new start
for all of us.</i>

08:05.152 --> 08:07.487
<i>Everybody finally gets
a fair chance.</i>

08:07.487 --> 08:11.450
Everybody gets a pony...
and a blow job.

08:11.450 --> 08:14.995
She sounds like she's running
for fucking prom queen.

08:14.995 --> 08:17.122
Who is going to be
your campaign manager?

08:17.122 --> 08:18.790
I'll pick someone soon enough.

08:18.790 --> 08:20.334
Take this seriously, love.

08:20.334 --> 08:22.377
You've never had to run
for office before.

08:22.377 --> 08:25.589
Nancy Gao has been preparing,
and she doesn't have to spend

08:25.589 --> 08:27.424
all her time
keeping the world safe.

08:27.424 --> 08:29.051
Don't worry.

08:29.051 --> 08:30.886
A nice, clean battle

08:30.886 --> 08:33.305
where I know
who the real enemy is?

08:33.305 --> 08:36.058
I'm looking forward to it.

08:36.058 --> 08:39.436
Tell Lipson I want an update
on Ilus the moment I land.

08:44.483 --> 08:46.818
[device beeping]

08:53.909 --> 08:55.410
[door clicking]

08:55.410 --> 08:56.453
David?

08:56.453 --> 08:57.454
[Benji] It's just me.

08:57.454 --> 08:58.622
[door clicks shut]

08:59.623 --> 09:00.874
You're home early.

09:00.874 --> 09:02.834
You talk to David today?

09:02.834 --> 09:04.670
He hasn't come back
from school yet.

09:04.670 --> 09:07.339
He's probably just studying
with his girlfriend.

09:07.339 --> 09:09.675
Can you get David to call me
when he gets home?

09:09.675 --> 09:11.218
Yeah, sure.

09:12.469 --> 09:13.595
Pick up some beer
on your way home.

09:13.595 --> 09:14.888
We're running low.

09:16.556 --> 09:17.641
Sure.

09:24.982 --> 09:28.318
- [device beeping]
- David, where are you?

09:28.318 --> 09:30.320
<i>[David] I'm sorry, Bobbie.
I'm really sorry.</i>

09:30.320 --> 09:32.197
<i>Please don't tell my parents,
but I-I-I need your help.</i>

09:32.197 --> 09:34.283
Okay, just slow down
and tell me what happened.

09:34.283 --> 09:36.451
<i>[David] I don't know. I was...
I was heading back from school</i>

09:36.451 --> 09:38.412
<i>and a couple guys
came up to me and they said</i>

09:38.412 --> 09:40.163
<i>that you had to be at
the Austin Shallows Concourse</i>

09:40.163 --> 09:41.581
<i>in 15 minutes.</i>

09:41.581 --> 09:42.916
I'll be there.
Don't worry.

09:42.916 --> 09:45.836
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

09:45.836 --> 09:48.255
<i>[woman] Correct.</i>

09:48.255 --> 09:50.090
<i>Correct.</i>

09:50.090 --> 09:54.052
<i>Check the connection
between the power cells.</i>

09:54.052 --> 09:55.053
<i>Correct.</i>

09:56.680 --> 09:58.015
<i>Correct.</i>

10:01.643 --> 10:03.186
<i>Incorrect.</i>

10:08.191 --> 10:10.068
You really fucked
things up for David.

10:10.068 --> 10:11.445
Where is he?

10:11.445 --> 10:12.863
At least now I don't have
to listen to him

10:12.863 --> 10:14.197
go on and on about you.

10:14.197 --> 10:15.657
It's fucking pathetic.

10:15.657 --> 10:16.783
You're gonna need
a lot more makeup

10:16.783 --> 10:18.076
if you don't tell me.

10:18.076 --> 10:19.828
[Esai] He's safe.

10:19.828 --> 10:22.497
But that can quickly change
if you don't cooperate.

10:22.497 --> 10:24.207
Who are you, her dad?

10:24.207 --> 10:26.793
I'm David's new
full-time employer.

10:27.919 --> 10:29.755
What are you talking about?

10:29.755 --> 10:32.007
David used to cook for me
after school.

10:32.007 --> 10:34.051
You gave him
a permanent position

10:34.051 --> 10:37.679
when you destroyed my lab
and cost me a lot of money.

10:37.679 --> 10:39.473
He's currently
working off that debt.

10:39.473 --> 10:42.017
Until I'm paid,
he isn't going anywhere.

10:42.017 --> 10:44.394
This is bullshit.
He's just a kid.

10:44.394 --> 10:46.563
Kid with a bright future
in terraforming.

10:46.563 --> 10:49.274
His parents are very proud,
from what I hear.

10:49.274 --> 10:51.651
Be a shame if you ruined
all that for him.

10:51.651 --> 10:52.611
<i>[woman] Correct.</i>

10:52.611 --> 10:53.653
What do you want?

10:53.653 --> 10:55.614
Just the money I lost.

10:55.614 --> 10:57.783
- I'd say that's fair.
- I don't have it.

10:57.783 --> 10:58.950
No,

10:58.950 --> 11:00.494
but you do have access

11:00.494 --> 11:02.871
to the military storage rooms
at the shipyard.

11:02.871 --> 11:04.122
All you need to do

11:04.122 --> 11:05.290
is accidentally leave

11:05.290 --> 11:07.834
one of the security doors open.

11:07.834 --> 11:10.837
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:10.837 --> 11:12.422
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:12.422 --> 11:14.091
Leave one of the doors open?
That's it?

11:14.091 --> 11:15.634
That's it.

11:15.634 --> 11:18.261
Do that, David's back
in school tomorrow.

11:19.554 --> 11:20.847
What are you stealing?

11:20.847 --> 11:22.516
That's none
of your fucking business.

11:22.516 --> 11:24.267
If it's weapons, I'm not gonna
help you hurt people.

11:24.267 --> 11:25.977
It isn't weapons.

11:25.977 --> 11:29.564
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:29.564 --> 11:32.442
Here are all the details
you need to know.

11:32.442 --> 11:34.236
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:34.236 --> 11:35.695
Why should I believe you?

11:35.695 --> 11:37.114
You shouldn't.

11:37.114 --> 11:38.573
But this is your only chance

11:38.573 --> 11:40.867
to have any control
of the situation.

11:40.867 --> 11:47.874
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:15.569 --> 12:19.239
[Naomi grunting]

12:19.239 --> 12:20.824
How's it going?

12:20.824 --> 12:22.242
Slow.

12:22.242 --> 12:24.995
These Belter generators
are old as shit.

12:24.995 --> 12:27.247
Lightning shorted
the junker out.

12:29.541 --> 12:31.877
Those fuckers aren't gonna do
a thing to help.

12:31.877 --> 12:33.128
Nope.

12:34.296 --> 12:36.923
I'd say the battle lines
have been drawn.

12:36.923 --> 12:40.051
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

12:40.051 --> 12:46.641
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:47.642 --> 12:50.645
[wind whistling]

13:12.792 --> 13:15.795
<i>[dark music]</i>

13:15.795 --> 13:22.511
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:43.949 --> 13:45.450
The eye hurt me.

13:45.450 --> 13:46.618
Were you laying against
something metal

13:46.618 --> 13:48.870
when the lightning happened?

13:48.870 --> 13:49.955
It hurt me.

13:49.955 --> 13:51.081
Maybe it's an allergy.

13:51.081 --> 13:53.416
I'll see what I can do.

13:53.416 --> 13:56.628
Jakob, Felcia, how much longer
before we have power?

13:56.628 --> 13:58.547
These meds are perishable.

13:58.547 --> 14:00.799
<i>[Naomi] Should be up
in a few minutes.</i>

14:02.467 --> 14:04.553
[breathing heavily]

14:04.553 --> 14:06.555
We're gonna need more of these.

14:06.555 --> 14:08.431
Those are
power converter modules.

14:08.431 --> 14:10.475
We have more
in the bag.

14:10.475 --> 14:12.269
Our light shuttle's
coming down.

14:12.269 --> 14:14.229
We'll tell them to bring
whatever's left.

14:14.229 --> 14:16.940
It won't be much,
but we're sending the <i>Barb</i>

14:16.940 --> 14:18.984
back through the Ring.

14:18.984 --> 14:20.277
When they sell our ore,
we'll have enough

14:20.277 --> 14:22.153
to buy years of supplies.

14:22.153 --> 14:24.072
Enough for all of us.

14:24.072 --> 14:25.574
It's a long trip
there and back.

14:25.574 --> 14:26.950
- Mm.
- Can you really

14:26.950 --> 14:28.994
- hold out until then?
- We'll make it.

14:28.994 --> 14:30.245
Ship's leaving as soon

14:30.245 --> 14:31.413
as the shuttle
gets back up.

14:31.413 --> 14:33.665
You're from the <i>Rocinante?</i>

14:33.665 --> 14:35.333
Yes.

14:35.333 --> 14:37.919
- Naomi.
- Naomi Nagata.

14:37.919 --> 14:39.796
She's their chief engineer.

14:39.796 --> 14:41.548
I told you about her.

14:42.716 --> 14:45.093
You went to university,
didn't you?

14:45.093 --> 14:48.096
Yes.
In the Belt.

14:48.096 --> 14:49.931
Nothing fancy
like Luna or Mars.

14:49.931 --> 14:53.852
But you got your degree.
That's what I want to do.

14:53.852 --> 14:56.062
- They think I can't.
[Jakob] We know you can.

14:56.062 --> 14:57.606
And one day w...

14:57.606 --> 14:58.982
We're not having
this conversation again.

14:58.982 --> 15:00.191
Lucia.

15:00.191 --> 15:01.610
We're building
a home here, Felcia.

15:01.610 --> 15:02.861
You need to accept that.

15:10.368 --> 15:12.329
I hate this place.

15:12.329 --> 15:15.040
Oh, it's not so bad.
I've lived in worse.

15:15.040 --> 15:16.875
We didn't have a choice.

15:16.875 --> 15:18.668
So now you understand
how I feel.

15:20.545 --> 15:22.297
Felcia, we're out
of disinfectant.

15:22.297 --> 15:24.090
Go get some alcohol
from the trading post.

15:24.090 --> 15:25.592
I'm helping Naomi.

15:25.592 --> 15:29.137
- I'll go.
- Felcia, do as you're told.

15:35.518 --> 15:37.062
I appreciate your help.

15:37.062 --> 15:39.230
But please
don't encourage her.

15:39.230 --> 15:41.858
She belongs with her family.

15:41.858 --> 15:44.861
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

15:44.861 --> 15:46.029
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:46.029 --> 15:47.864
Tonight we do this.

15:47.864 --> 15:49.574
Yeah?

15:49.574 --> 15:53.161
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:53.161 --> 15:54.454
I'll be back.

15:55.830 --> 15:58.583
[power tools whirring]

15:58.583 --> 16:01.836
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:01.836 --> 16:03.380
Lucia, I got a thing going,

16:03.380 --> 16:05.048
rounding up some people
for later today.

16:05.048 --> 16:06.633
Are you crazy?
You were right there.

16:06.633 --> 16:08.009
You saw what happened
to Coop.

16:08.009 --> 16:10.053
Yeah. That the reason
we must do this now.

16:10.053 --> 16:11.763
- Find someone else.
- No.

16:11.763 --> 16:12.847
Hey, Lucia,

16:12.847 --> 16:14.849
<i>you're part of this.</i>

16:14.849 --> 16:16.976
<i>[Lucia] No, Scotty.
Leave me out of it.</i>

16:16.976 --> 16:19.396
<i>[Scotty] Murtry is gonna pay
for what he did.</i>

16:19.396 --> 16:21.022
<i>You better be there.</i>

16:21.022 --> 16:24.567
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:24.567 --> 16:26.277
[electricity sparking]

16:26.277 --> 16:27.779
Shit.

16:42.711 --> 16:45.130
[breathing heavily]

16:45.130 --> 16:52.137
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:52.137 --> 16:54.222
[device clicks]

16:54.222 --> 16:55.432
[exhales sharply]

16:55.432 --> 16:57.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:57.809 --> 16:58.810
Naomi.

17:00.228 --> 17:03.565
I just fried an isolator.
Do you have one I can borrow?

17:03.565 --> 17:05.024
[Naomi] I'm all out.
Sorry.

17:06.151 --> 17:08.069
[man] Hey, on the perimeter.

17:08.069 --> 17:10.363
Perimeter,
gear check over there?

17:10.363 --> 17:11.239
Yeah, looks good.

17:11.990 --> 17:13.158
That's okay.

17:30.633 --> 17:31.843
What do you think
you're doing?

17:32.635 --> 17:34.512
I need some parts.

17:34.512 --> 17:37.849
All RCE equipment
stays here.

17:37.849 --> 17:39.434
Well, you're not using it.

17:39.434 --> 17:41.102
Murtry's orders.

17:42.854 --> 17:44.814
You serious?
It's a fucking generator.

17:44.814 --> 17:47.317
And it's ours.
Put it down now.

17:48.818 --> 17:49.819
Sure.

17:50.445 --> 17:51.905
- [grunts]
- [blows landing]

17:51.905 --> 17:53.698
[both grunting]

17:54.449 --> 17:56.659
All right, that's enough!
That's enough!

17:56.659 --> 17:57.911
Just let him take it.

17:57.911 --> 17:59.245
Murtry said...

17:59.245 --> 18:00.705
Yeah, I'll square it
with Murtry.

18:02.290 --> 18:04.125
What the fuck, Amos?

18:04.125 --> 18:05.293
What?

18:05.293 --> 18:06.795
You like getting shot?

18:06.795 --> 18:09.130
- No.
- 'Cause you were about to.

18:10.173 --> 18:13.259
I needed some parts
and you weren't using it.

18:13.259 --> 18:15.678
Listen, Murtry's my boss.
My job is to follow orders.

18:15.678 --> 18:17.096
So don't think
I won't shoot you

18:17.096 --> 18:19.516
if you pull that kind
of shit again.

18:19.516 --> 18:20.558
Okay.

18:22.560 --> 18:24.604
So does that mean
we're not fucking anymore?

18:26.064 --> 18:27.023
What?

18:29.067 --> 18:32.612
Uh, no, it...no, I guess.

18:33.988 --> 18:35.490
Cool.

18:35.490 --> 18:36.783
See you later, then?

18:49.295 --> 18:51.965
They believe the lightning
was artificially generated.

18:51.965 --> 18:53.341
Hmm.

18:53.341 --> 18:55.218
But how and why
is still unknown.

18:56.219 --> 18:58.096
Holden says
he's investigating.

18:58.096 --> 19:00.974
Hmm.
And that's all?

19:01.933 --> 19:03.309
That's all.

19:03.309 --> 19:04.477
[device beeps]

19:07.564 --> 19:09.148
Keep me apprised.

19:10.275 --> 19:13.278
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:13.278 --> 19:19.868
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:19.868 --> 19:22.370
Madam Secretary, it has been
an honor to serve you.

19:22.370 --> 19:24.289
Your resignation is accepted.

19:25.206 --> 19:27.333
I am surprised you have
the time to waste

19:27.333 --> 19:29.544
on such meaningless traditions
like this.

19:29.544 --> 19:31.796
There's been another
incident on Ilus.

19:31.796 --> 19:33.006
New Terra.

19:34.257 --> 19:37.635
That's what our citizens
call it, in case you forgot.

19:37.635 --> 19:40.138
Does its name change
what's happening there?

19:40.138 --> 19:41.806
Of course not.

19:41.806 --> 19:43.474
Because we don't know
what's happening there.

19:43.474 --> 19:46.185
None of us do.
Which is my goddamn point.

19:46.185 --> 19:48.688
Colonizations of the Ring
systems is inevitable.

19:48.688 --> 19:50.565
And whatever is out there,
we'll deal with it

19:50.565 --> 19:52.609
because that is the history
of our species.

19:52.609 --> 19:56.404
Right up to the moment that
our species ceases to exist.

19:57.155 --> 19:59.782
I look forward to having
this debate with you in public.

20:01.034 --> 20:02.327
So do I.

20:02.327 --> 20:09.334
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:21.846 --> 20:24.974
<i>[woman]
Unity, strength, honor.</i>

20:24.974 --> 20:26.643
<i>The Martian Marines.</i>

20:26.643 --> 20:28.186
<i>Join today.</i>

20:28.186 --> 20:35.193
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:43.242 --> 20:46.829
[computer beeping]

20:46.829 --> 20:49.248
I want to report a kidnapping.

20:49.248 --> 20:51.042
And what's
the missing person's name?

20:51.042 --> 20:52.961
David Draper.

20:52.961 --> 20:54.921
Where and when
was he last seen?

20:54.921 --> 20:57.548
Uh, yesterday
in Innis Shallows.

20:57.548 --> 20:59.717
The kidnapper contacted me
this morning.

20:59.717 --> 21:01.678
So it's also
a ransom situation?

21:01.678 --> 21:05.598
Yes.
Well, yes and no.

21:06.641 --> 21:08.518
[computer beeping]

21:08.518 --> 21:10.728
[door buzzes]
A detective will see you now.

21:12.313 --> 21:13.481
[computer beeping]

21:15.858 --> 21:18.653
[Esai] I understand you want
to report a kidnapping?

21:18.653 --> 21:21.364
I'm Detective Esai Martin.

21:21.364 --> 21:23.408
A goddamn cop.

21:23.408 --> 21:27.537
With an immaculate record
and a high conviction rate.

21:27.537 --> 21:31.541
You're a disgraced and
dishonorably discharged marine

21:31.541 --> 21:33.876
with a wild story
about drug dealers

21:33.876 --> 21:37.296
kidnapping and extorting
your nephew.

21:37.296 --> 21:39.465
Don't need focus drugs
to know how that ends.

21:39.465 --> 21:42.343
How'd you know I'd go
to the police?

21:42.343 --> 21:43.511
You're a good Martian.

21:44.762 --> 21:48.474
I hope you now understand
the severity of the situation.

21:49.892 --> 21:51.519
Your word may be worth
more than mine,

21:51.519 --> 21:53.938
but there are cameras
all over that shipyard.

21:53.938 --> 21:56.190
I'll get caught
and you'll be fucked.

21:56.190 --> 21:58.985
Cameras at that dock
have been glitchy for years.

21:58.985 --> 22:01.696
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:01.696 --> 22:04.240
So you can control
any of these?

22:04.240 --> 22:06.576
Malfunctions happen
all the time.

22:06.576 --> 22:08.536
Or maybe they don't
and you'll have footage

22:08.536 --> 22:10.204
to keep blackmailing
David and me.

22:11.914 --> 22:13.875
I never even thought of that.

22:13.875 --> 22:17.211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:17.211 --> 22:18.379
[sighs]

22:18.379 --> 22:20.048
This better be a one-time deal.

22:20.048 --> 22:22.925
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:22.925 --> 22:25.887
Come again for David or for me,
bring a gun.

22:25.887 --> 22:27.972
I don't wanna kill
an unarmed man.

22:29.057 --> 22:30.016
[computer beeps]

22:30.016 --> 22:32.101
Thanks for coming in.

22:32.101 --> 22:34.896
We'll do all we can to get your
nephew back safe and sound.

22:34.896 --> 22:41.903
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:42.570 --> 22:45.698
[engine revving]

22:46.783 --> 22:49.118
<i>[Elvi] The instruments
on the</i> Edward Israel <i>indicate</i>

22:49.118 --> 22:51.204
that there's definitely
some kind of structure

22:51.204 --> 22:53.372
directly below the path
of the lightning,

22:53.372 --> 22:55.875
several kilometers below.

22:55.875 --> 22:57.460
Jesus.

22:57.460 --> 22:59.337
That's one hell
of a circuit you connected.

23:00.797 --> 23:02.381
What do you mean by that?

23:02.381 --> 23:04.175
Nothing.
It's just a figure of speech.

23:05.218 --> 23:07.303
[device beeps]

23:07.303 --> 23:09.430
You seem to know a lot more
than you're telling me.

23:09.430 --> 23:11.182
Why is that?

23:11.182 --> 23:13.184
I'm really not at liberty
to discuss it.

23:13.184 --> 23:14.560
<i>[Fayez] Hey, guys.</i>

23:14.560 --> 23:17.688
It stopped.
The lightning stopped.

23:17.688 --> 23:19.315
The last strikes
were at the chain of islands

23:19.315 --> 23:21.067
on the other side
of the planet.

23:22.110 --> 23:25.446
So...crisis averted.

23:25.446 --> 23:27.657
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

23:27.657 --> 23:29.367
[Elvi] Fayez,
we need to monitor as many

23:29.367 --> 23:31.619
of the lightning strike
locations as we possibly can.

23:31.619 --> 23:33.621
Full spectrum imaging.

23:33.621 --> 23:40.628
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:41.504 --> 23:44.799
[ground rumbling]

23:44.799 --> 23:45.925
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:45.925 --> 23:48.302
Oh.

23:48.302 --> 23:50.096
- [Holden] Do y'all feel that?
- [Elvi] Yes.

23:50.096 --> 23:52.181
I was hoping
it was just me.

23:52.181 --> 23:55.393
Fayez, it felt like we just
experienced an earthquake.

23:55.393 --> 23:57.019
That's impossible.

23:57.019 --> 23:58.938
This planet
has no tectonic activity.

23:58.938 --> 24:00.773
<i>[Holden] But we all felt it.</i>

24:00.773 --> 24:03.985
<i>[Fayez] Elvi, is my geo-kit
still on your cart?</i>

24:03.985 --> 24:06.112
- Yes, it's there.
<i>[Fayez] Good.</i>

24:06.112 --> 24:08.030
<i>There are three
seismometer spikes in it.</i>

24:08.030 --> 24:09.657
<i>Plant one where you are now</i>

24:09.657 --> 24:11.284
<i>and the other two
as far apart as you can.</i>

24:11.284 --> 24:13.452
<i>Fifty-kilometer
minimum separation.</i>

24:13.452 --> 24:16.247
<i>Do that, and I can pinpoint
the source of the quake.</i>

24:16.247 --> 24:17.373
Okay.

24:18.791 --> 24:20.543
Guess we're going
for a ride.

24:20.543 --> 24:27.550
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:28.426 --> 24:30.595
[panel clicks]

24:30.595 --> 24:34.056
[power whirring]

24:36.767 --> 24:39.770
[indistinct chatter]

24:46.485 --> 24:48.863
You attacked some
of my people here today.

24:50.740 --> 24:52.366
Yep.

24:52.366 --> 24:54.702
When you undermine
my team's authority,

24:54.702 --> 24:56.370
you put everybody here
in danger,

24:56.370 --> 24:57.872
including your own crew.

25:00.124 --> 25:01.209
Is that a threat?

25:03.628 --> 25:06.631
I'm just making sure
you understand the situation.

25:06.631 --> 25:10.009
I do...Murtry.

25:10.009 --> 25:13.471
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:13.471 --> 25:15.765
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:15.765 --> 25:19.894
The others don't get it yet,
but, uh, I know what you are.

25:19.894 --> 25:21.312
Oh?

25:21.312 --> 25:23.773
And what is that?

25:23.773 --> 25:25.566
A killer.

25:25.566 --> 25:29.570
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:29.570 --> 25:31.155
[groans softly]

25:31.155 --> 25:35.326
You have all the excuses
that make you seem right.

25:35.326 --> 25:37.578
But the truth is,

25:37.578 --> 25:39.288
your dick got hard
when you smoked that guy

25:39.288 --> 25:40.915
in front of everybody,

25:40.915 --> 25:44.335
and you can't wait
to do it again.

25:44.335 --> 25:46.796
Speaking from experience?

25:46.796 --> 25:48.839
Not really.

25:48.839 --> 25:51.592
But from one killer to another,

25:51.592 --> 25:54.971
you don't wanna try that shit
with my people.

25:54.971 --> 25:58.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:58.349 --> 26:01.435
Someday I think you and I
are going to end up bloody.

26:01.435 --> 26:03.145
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:03.145 --> 26:05.606
How about now?

26:05.606 --> 26:08.067
I'm free right now.

26:08.067 --> 26:14.949
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:30.923 --> 26:34.552
For the first time in history,
Mars and Earth are united

26:34.552 --> 26:37.930
and now everyone
wants to up and leave.

26:37.930 --> 26:39.598
Well, we could always
go with them,

26:39.598 --> 26:41.434
get away from all this.

26:41.434 --> 26:43.811
You've already saved the world
once from destruction.

26:43.811 --> 26:46.022
Any second act
can only disappoint.

26:50.276 --> 26:51.902
[elevator dings]

26:51.902 --> 26:54.697
Well, at least then
I'd finally get to cash in

26:54.697 --> 26:56.949
the thousands
of foot massages you owe me.

26:56.949 --> 26:59.076
Oh, I think you're mistaken,
Madam Secretary.

26:59.076 --> 27:01.287
I only owe you around 1,500.

27:01.287 --> 27:02.496
Oh.
[laughs]

27:02.496 --> 27:05.374
[water running]

27:05.374 --> 27:06.500
[monitor beeping]

27:06.500 --> 27:08.169
[Avasarala] It should be more.

27:08.169 --> 27:10.296
It's a comfortable lead.

27:13.132 --> 27:14.967
I'm not one to say
I told you so.

27:14.967 --> 27:16.093
Yes, you are.

27:17.636 --> 27:18.846
Fine.

27:18.846 --> 27:21.432
But if people
vote in Nancy Gao,

27:21.432 --> 27:24.060
they'll be inviting
another Eros.

27:24.060 --> 27:25.895
[doorbell rings]

27:25.895 --> 27:26.812
Come.

27:26.812 --> 27:27.813
[door clicks open]

27:27.813 --> 27:29.106
[footsteps approaching]

27:29.106 --> 27:30.649
[Diaz]
Apologies for the interruption.

27:30.649 --> 27:32.276
I have the research
you requested.

27:34.195 --> 27:37.281
- He's part of the campaign.
- Of course.

27:37.281 --> 27:39.283
- [monitor beeping]
- Our friends have been doing

27:39.283 --> 27:41.369
quite a bit of digging
into Nancy Gao.

27:41.369 --> 27:43.579
[Avasarala] I know all this.

27:43.579 --> 27:45.289
From rags to riches,
top of her class,

27:45.289 --> 27:47.666
blah, blah, blah.

27:47.666 --> 27:49.627
It gets more interesting
where it talks about her

27:49.627 --> 27:51.379
growing up on Basic.

27:51.379 --> 27:53.047
She scored very high marks
on her placement test

27:53.047 --> 27:54.173
and got into
the apprentice lottery.

27:54.173 --> 27:55.591
I don't have time or patience

27:55.591 --> 27:57.718
to read her whole
fucking biography.

27:57.718 --> 27:59.678
Just tell me
what you found on her.

27:59.678 --> 28:02.014
Nancy Gao was accepted
into the apprentice lottery

28:02.014 --> 28:04.475
on her first try.

28:04.475 --> 28:06.727
One week after she applied.

28:06.727 --> 28:08.854
No one's that lucky.

28:08.854 --> 28:11.107
Some people wait decades.

28:11.107 --> 28:13.651
We found an addendum
attached to her application

28:13.651 --> 28:16.529
from former
Secretary of Education Javid

28:16.529 --> 28:18.239
formally requesting
that her application

28:18.239 --> 28:19.949
be given
special consideration.

28:19.949 --> 28:22.201
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

28:22.201 --> 28:24.453
She jumped the line.

28:24.453 --> 28:26.872
She cheated.

28:26.872 --> 28:28.541
What do you want
to do with this?

28:28.541 --> 28:30.584
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:30.584 --> 28:33.212
Leak it.
Discreetly.

28:33.212 --> 28:35.464
The media will uncover
the rest.

28:36.257 --> 28:39.051
Gao says people
deserve the truth.

28:39.051 --> 28:41.470
Let's give it to them.

28:41.470 --> 28:48.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:49.937 --> 28:53.107
[power tool whirring]

28:53.107 --> 29:00.114
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:00.114 --> 29:04.034
[keypad beeping]

29:04.034 --> 29:05.286
[lock clicks]

29:05.286 --> 29:12.293
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:20.551 --> 29:23.929
[device beeping]

29:23.929 --> 29:28.642
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:28.642 --> 29:30.895
[keypad beeping]

29:30.895 --> 29:32.104
[lock clicks]

29:32.104 --> 29:37.359
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:37.359 --> 29:39.028
[device beeping]

29:39.028 --> 29:46.035
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:01.091 --> 30:04.094
<i>[intense music]</i>

30:04.094 --> 30:11.101
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:28.619 --> 30:35.626
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:41.465 --> 30:43.259
[device beeping]

30:43.259 --> 30:45.177
[whirring]

30:45.177 --> 30:49.557
[wind whistling]

30:49.557 --> 30:51.308
Third seismometer is online.

30:51.308 --> 30:53.644
All right, let's see
where it's coming from.

30:53.644 --> 30:57.273
[computer beeping]

30:57.273 --> 31:00.651
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

31:00.651 --> 31:05.489
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:05.489 --> 31:06.532
Okay.

31:06.532 --> 31:07.658
<i>I've got the epicenter.</i>

31:07.658 --> 31:08.993
<i>I'll send the coordinates.</i>

31:08.993 --> 31:10.452
[device beeps]

31:10.452 --> 31:17.209
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:25.593 --> 31:28.596
[power tools whirring]

31:36.186 --> 31:37.563
Thanks.

31:39.815 --> 31:44.445
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:44.445 --> 31:46.864
[scanner beeping]

31:46.864 --> 31:53.871
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:55.205 --> 31:58.042
[scanner beeping]

31:58.042 --> 32:04.340
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:04.340 --> 32:07.176
[scanner beeping]

32:07.176 --> 32:14.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:27.863 --> 32:30.157
[scanner beeping]

32:30.157 --> 32:31.992
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:31.992 --> 32:34.244
[scanner beeping]

32:34.244 --> 32:35.746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:35.746 --> 32:38.332
[scanner beeping]

32:38.332 --> 32:40.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:40.834 --> 32:44.630
[device beeping]

32:44.630 --> 32:51.637
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:08.195 --> 33:11.532
<i>[man]</i> Barbapiccola <i>to shuttle,
you are clear to return.</i>

33:11.532 --> 33:14.535
[rocket engine roaring]

33:19.540 --> 33:21.208
[Murtry] This a bad time?

33:24.753 --> 33:26.171
No.

33:28.340 --> 33:30.050
Can I help you with something?

33:30.050 --> 33:32.594
You're the only one who can.

33:35.806 --> 33:38.267
Swelling on my leg's gone down
faster than you said it would.

33:38.267 --> 33:41.353
Uh, brace needs adjusting.

33:41.353 --> 33:42.646
You must be a quick healer.

33:46.567 --> 33:48.944
Come on.
Let me take a look at it.

33:52.990 --> 33:54.616
[door clicks open]

33:57.411 --> 33:58.871
[door clicks shut]

34:02.666 --> 34:04.877
Payment for services rendered.

34:05.753 --> 34:07.796
No need to barter.

34:08.797 --> 34:10.299
Well, I never got a chance
to thank you

34:10.299 --> 34:11.884
for all your help
at the crash site.

34:11.884 --> 34:14.386
You...you got there fast.

34:15.596 --> 34:17.556
Only doing my job.

34:35.115 --> 34:37.326
[tool clicking]

34:37.326 --> 34:40.120
I've noticed you talk
a lot to Scotty.

34:42.247 --> 34:44.249
I talk with a lot of people.

34:44.249 --> 34:46.084
Part of the job.

34:47.753 --> 34:49.379
They trust you,

34:49.379 --> 34:51.340
take you into their confidence.

34:52.466 --> 34:55.093
I'm a med tech,
not a priest.

35:03.143 --> 35:04.269
How's that?

35:05.521 --> 35:07.314
That is better.
Thank you.

35:08.941 --> 35:11.068
Come back if you want it
adjusted again.

35:18.992 --> 35:21.620
I don't want any more violence.

35:21.620 --> 35:23.205
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:23.205 --> 35:26.792
Just the truth
and a peaceful resolution.

35:26.792 --> 35:32.881
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:32.881 --> 35:35.717
I sense you feel the same way.

35:35.717 --> 35:37.469
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:37.469 --> 35:39.805
[door clicks open]

35:39.805 --> 35:41.932
What are you
doing in here?

35:41.932 --> 35:43.809
Getting some help.

35:45.477 --> 35:47.354
You can't help us

35:47.354 --> 35:49.147
and now you want us
to help you?

35:49.147 --> 35:51.400
Just having a conversation.

35:51.400 --> 35:53.819
Like you were
with the man you shot?

35:53.819 --> 35:56.613
Belters, you always
play the victim.

35:56.613 --> 35:58.282
Well, we've had
a lot of practice

35:58.282 --> 36:00.242
because of men like you.

36:00.242 --> 36:02.911
Men who think our lives are
disposable for your own gains.

36:02.911 --> 36:05.038
Your lives?
I had 23 of mine

36:05.038 --> 36:06.832
in the ground
before they even set foot on...

36:06.832 --> 36:08.375
- [table bangs]
- That doesn't give you

36:08.375 --> 36:10.919
the right to play judge, jury,
and executioner!

36:10.919 --> 36:13.463
Not while we're here!

36:13.463 --> 36:15.340
You're not gonna get away...

36:15.340 --> 36:18.969
[breathing heavily]

36:18.969 --> 36:20.888
- [gasping]
- Naomi!

36:20.888 --> 36:23.181
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:23.181 --> 36:24.349
[Lucia] Okay, come on.

36:24.349 --> 36:28.061
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:28.061 --> 36:30.647
[computer beeping]

36:30.647 --> 36:37.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:37.070 --> 36:39.114
[Fayez] Guys, do you see this?

36:39.114 --> 36:41.491
<i>You should be on top of it.</i>

36:41.491 --> 36:43.327
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:43.327 --> 36:46.455
Holy shit.

36:46.455 --> 36:53.462
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:53.462 --> 36:56.465
[ground rumbling]

36:56.465 --> 36:59.593
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:59.593 --> 37:01.345
<i>[woman] Please stand clear
of the doors.</i>

37:01.345 --> 37:03.430
<i>This car will be
departing shortly.</i>

37:03.430 --> 37:07.267
<i>[woman speaking
a Chinese language]</i>

37:07.267 --> 37:09.978
- Where's David?
- Something's come up.

37:09.978 --> 37:11.730
This was a one-time deal.

37:11.730 --> 37:13.357
There's something
we need to discuss.

37:13.357 --> 37:15.359
- My buyers...
- The Belters?

37:15.359 --> 37:16.985
OPA, by my guess.

37:16.985 --> 37:18.362
Their politics
don't bother me.

37:18.362 --> 37:20.822
Where's David?

37:20.822 --> 37:23.283
Back home safe and sound.

37:24.743 --> 37:26.328
[device beeping]

37:26.328 --> 37:28.413
<i>[David] Bobbie, I'm okay.
I'm home.</i>

37:28.413 --> 37:30.415
Okay, just stay there and...
and keep the door locked.

37:30.415 --> 37:32.584
- I'll be back soon.
- [device beeps]

37:40.550 --> 37:42.719
Why didn't you just tell me
you'd let him go?

37:42.719 --> 37:45.806
I wanted to see how far I could
push you before you shivved me.

37:49.393 --> 37:52.062
When we get to Innis Shallows,
I better not see you again.

37:52.062 --> 37:54.731
You know, a person with your
training and skill set

37:54.731 --> 37:56.358
could make a lot of money.

37:56.358 --> 37:59.569
- I have a job.
- Yeah, tearing down warships.

37:59.569 --> 38:02.114
Wasting the best technology
in the system.

38:02.114 --> 38:04.074
- Very noble.
- Somebody's gotta do it.

38:04.074 --> 38:05.367
Look around you.

38:05.367 --> 38:06.827
Mars is changing.

38:06.827 --> 38:09.287
The Ring gates
are the new great hope.

38:09.287 --> 38:12.499
All those sensors and guidance
systems we built for war,

38:12.499 --> 38:14.960
they're sitting in warehouses
gathering dust,

38:14.960 --> 38:17.129
waiting for you
to throw them out.

38:17.129 --> 38:19.172
They could be used
by millions of people

38:19.172 --> 38:21.550
to do something better
with their lives.

38:21.550 --> 38:23.885
And make you rich?

38:23.885 --> 38:25.595
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:25.595 --> 38:27.389
Very noble.

38:27.389 --> 38:29.891
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:29.891 --> 38:32.978
After what they did to you,

38:32.978 --> 38:35.105
you don't owe
this place anything.

38:35.105 --> 38:37.274
- [P.A. system beeps]
<i>- [woman] Arriving now...</i>

38:37.274 --> 38:39.151
I'm not a criminal.

38:39.151 --> 38:40.736
<i>[woman] Please stand clear
of the doors.</i>

38:40.736 --> 38:43.530
Mars is gonna need
a lot more people like you.

38:44.656 --> 38:47.659
<i>[woman speaking
a Chinese language]</i>

38:47.659 --> 38:54.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:01.465 --> 39:03.133
<i>[Scotty]
When it dark,</i>

39:03.133 --> 39:05.844
Asha and I set up
behind their module.

39:05.844 --> 39:09.598
On my signal, Kellan and Enzo
open fire from the front,

39:09.598 --> 39:11.099
flush them out the back.

39:11.099 --> 39:13.101
Then we finish this.

39:13.101 --> 39:14.936
What about Lucia?

39:14.936 --> 39:17.564
You said she in on this.

39:17.564 --> 39:20.567
Yeah.
She with us.

39:20.567 --> 39:22.235
Whether she think so or no.

39:29.868 --> 39:32.496
[coughing]

39:32.496 --> 39:34.081
Stay down.
Stay down.

39:34.081 --> 39:35.457
I need to...

39:35.457 --> 39:37.793
I thought you were having
a heart attack.

39:37.793 --> 39:40.170
I'm just acclimating
to the gravity, so...

39:40.170 --> 39:41.338
Ah-ah!

39:41.338 --> 39:44.341
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

39:44.341 --> 39:49.054
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:49.054 --> 39:50.639
A few days after we landed,

39:50.639 --> 39:53.517
a dozen people
from the <i>Barb</i> collapsed.

39:53.517 --> 39:55.018
We realized their bodies

39:55.018 --> 39:58.188
had not responded
to the gravity drugs.

39:58.188 --> 40:00.524
I'll be fine.

40:00.524 --> 40:02.359
Two of ours
who said the same thing

40:02.359 --> 40:05.737
were put in the recycler
less than a day later.

40:05.737 --> 40:08.031
[sighs]

40:08.031 --> 40:11.368
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:11.368 --> 40:13.495
You don't go back up
the well soon,

40:13.495 --> 40:16.873
you'll be dead,
just like them.

40:16.873 --> 40:23.880
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:32.722 --> 40:35.725
[ground rumbling]

40:37.144 --> 40:39.146
[Alex] That thing
is chewing up a swath

40:39.146 --> 40:40.856
over three kilometers wide.

40:40.856 --> 40:42.524
If it continues
on its current course,

40:42.524 --> 40:44.025
it's gonna clip the edge
of the settlement.

40:44.025 --> 40:45.235
They're gonna get flattened.

40:47.195 --> 40:50.282
This might be a good time
to talk to Miller.

40:50.282 --> 40:52.826
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

40:52.826 --> 40:59.833
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:20.896 --> 41:24.065
Alex, link in to the <i>Roci's</i>
fire controls.

41:24.065 --> 41:25.525
We're gonna drop a torpedo
on that thing.

41:25.525 --> 41:27.569
- Conventional warhead.
- What?

41:27.569 --> 41:28.904
Aye, aye, Cap.

41:28.904 --> 41:30.447
No, no, no.
You...you can't do that.

41:30.447 --> 41:31.823
Watch us.

41:31.823 --> 41:33.491
Well, we...we are
witnessing something

41:33.491 --> 41:35.410
that human beings
have never seen before.

41:35.410 --> 41:37.204
And your first instinct
is to destroy it?

41:37.204 --> 41:39.122
Yeah, before it destroys us.

41:39.122 --> 41:41.625
No, there has to be something
underneath powering it.

41:41.625 --> 41:43.960
Meaning something
immensely powerful.

41:43.960 --> 41:45.921
What if that blows up too?

41:45.921 --> 41:48.173
We still have time. We could
go back to the settlement.

41:48.173 --> 41:49.716
- We could evacuate.
- And in the meantime,

41:49.716 --> 41:51.301
that thing could speed up,
change course,

41:51.301 --> 41:52.677
do something else
we can't even imagine,

41:52.677 --> 41:54.137
and then we'd be
out of options.

41:54.137 --> 41:55.597
We can't take that chance.

41:55.597 --> 41:57.557
- All right, torpedo's ready.
- Fire.

41:57.557 --> 42:01.853
- [device beeps]
- [torpedo blasting]

42:01.853 --> 42:04.231
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:04.231 --> 42:07.234
[torpedo roaring]

42:07.234 --> 42:14.241
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:16.451 --> 42:20.455
[torpedo roaring]

42:24.584 --> 42:28.713
[booming]

42:28.713 --> 42:33.468
[ground rumbling]

42:33.468 --> 42:36.721
[booming]

42:49.693 --> 42:51.361
[ground rumbling]

42:51.361 --> 42:52.862
The fuck that?

42:52.862 --> 42:54.698
<i>Na sasa.</i>

42:54.698 --> 42:56.074
Come, we go.

42:56.074 --> 42:58.243
[glass shattering]

42:58.243 --> 42:59.202
[smoke bomb hissing]

42:59.202 --> 43:00.745
[man coughing]

43:00.745 --> 43:02.580
[Scotty] Get out!
Get out now!

43:02.580 --> 43:04.499
[all coughing]

43:06.626 --> 43:08.670
- [gunfire]
- [all grunting]

43:08.670 --> 43:12.299
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:12.299 --> 43:15.343
- [gunfire]
- [groaning]

43:15.343 --> 43:16.678
[shouts]

43:16.678 --> 43:18.430
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:18.430 --> 43:19.264
[grunting]

43:19.264 --> 43:22.309
[people shouting]

43:22.309 --> 43:28.356
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:28.356 --> 43:31.359
[Scotty groaning]

43:31.359 --> 43:34.863
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:34.863 --> 43:36.948
[gagging]

43:40.160 --> 43:42.829
[gagging]

43:43.705 --> 43:45.915
I hope that answers
your question.

43:48.460 --> 43:50.837
[gunshot]

43:52.505 --> 43:55.508
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

43:55.508 --> 44:02.515
<i>♪ ♪</i>
